<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-58-0646 </DOCNO><TEXT>A 3-year-old boy with focal nodular hyperplasia of the liver underwentsonography, computed tomography, scintigraphy and angiography. Amongthese procedures single photon emission computed tomography was helpfulin the detection of the lesion and in making a more confident diagnosisof the disease, with its capability to demonstrate the presence of thereticuloendothelial cells within the lesion.</TEXT></DOC>